items.name: Instant Foods Annie's Homegrown Organic Macaroni And Cheese
items.display_name: Annie's Homegrown Organic Macaroni And Cheese
items.directions: Annie's Way in 10 Minutes: 1. Boil: 6 cups water in a medium saucepan. 2. Stir In: pasta, bring to boil. Cook 8-10 minutes, or until done, stirring occasionally. 3. Drain Pasta: in colander. While pasta is draining, 4. Add: 3 tbsp lowfat milk to the warm saucepan. (Optional: Add 2 tbsp unsalted butter for richer flavor). 5. Sprinkle: cheese over milk; stir to combine. 6. Add: cooked pasta back to saucepan and stir well. Enjoy! Annie's Suggestions: For a richer flavor, add 2 tbsp unsalted butter. For a creamy, tangy version, replace milk with 1/2 cup lowfat yogurt. Keep in a cool, dry place.

items.name: Instant Foods Annies Homegrown Org Wisconsin Cheddar Grass Fed Mac & Cheese
items.display_name: Annies Homegrown Org Wisconsin Cheddar Grass Fed Mac & Cheese
items.details:
The Goodness of Grass-Fed Cheese...humanely raised cows graze on pasture grasses...enhancing the flavor and nutrition of their organic milk...made into organic cheese and...combined with organic pasta...to make your meal wonderfully wholesome & delicious!
Meet Bernie! Bernie was Annie's pet Dutch rabbit. When she started the company, Annie chose him to be our official "rabbit of approval" representing the simplicity, care and goodness in all of our products.
Meet Our Bernie-Approved Farmers: Fresh out of college, we combined what little savings we had, bought a herd of 40 Jersey cows and began our lives dairying in the fertile valley of Ferndale, California. Twenty-five years and four children later, we are proud to be farmers for Rumiano Cheese Company, who makes grass-fed cheese for Annie's. Our cows are grass fed, roaming freely throughout our green pastures. We are most proud that our dairy is fully organic certified, which means we don't use any persistent toxic pesticides, synthetic fertilizers, or GMO's when producing our milk. We love raising healthy cows, which makes for great cheese! Sincerely, Jim + Jacque.
We work with trusted suppliers to source only non-GMO ingredients. Whole Grain Stamp: 8g or more per serving.

items.details:
The Goodness of Grass Fed Cheese...humanely raised cows graze on pasture grasses...enhancing the flavor and nutrition of their organic milk...made into organic cheese and...combined with organic pasta...to make your meal wonderfully wholesome & delicious!
Meet Bernie! Bernie was Annie's pet Dutch rabbit. When she started the company, Annie chose him to be our official "rabbit of approval" representing the simplicity, care and goodness in all of our products.
Meet Our Bernie-Approved Farmers: Fresh out of college, we combined what little savings we had, bought a herd of 40 Jersey cows and began our lives dairying in the fertile valley of Ferndale, California. Twenty-five years and four children later, we are proud to be farmers for Rumiano Cheese Company, who makes grass-fed cheese for Annie's. Our cows are grass fed, roaming freely throughout our green pastures. We are most proud that our dairy is fully organic certified, which means we don't use any persistent toxic pesticides, synthetic fertilizers, or GMO's when producing our milk. We love raising healthy cows, which makes for great cheese! Sincerely, Jim + Jacque.
We work with trusted suppliers to source only non-GMO ingredients. Whole Grain Stamp: 8g or more per serving.
